The paper discusses Bag of Features (BoF) approaches for computer vision tasks, specifically image classification and retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses techniques for mitigating quantization errors, improving feature detection, and speeding up image retrieval, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of BoF methods in video search and robot localization, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.AI).
